This is not very generic:
  * The case `dnf` vs. `dfn` vs. any other similar typo is already taken care of by the `no_command` rule;
  * The case of `istall` vs. `install` should be taken care of with `utils.get_closest` and a list of possible candidates (I guess there is more to `dnf` than just an `install` subcommand).

custom = {
